The creak of a door interrupted Cody just as he started moving again. He frowned and looked behind himself uneasily. “This would be much simpler tactically if nothing else in here had opposable thumbs,” he muttered. “I wonder if there's a spell for that?” He thought about it briefly, then shook his head. “If there was, there would probably be a heart removal spell, and I think I would have heard about that.”
